  "text": "If κ (resp. μ) is negative, p μ,κ βT,n,N,ξ may be infinite at τ = 0 (resp. τ = 1). In the previous Section 4.2 we choose w 0 = 0 (resp. w m = 0) so as to avoid this problem. But this choice of w 0 and w m implies an error (see [CITATION_1] ). In order to reduce this error, we replace the term ",
